      <bioghist id="aspace_bab48cca253cbd3c55b65068e00399e4">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Joseph W. Lee (1894-1987) and Nancy L. Kim Lee (1900-1978) immigrated to the United States from Korea in 1906 and 1916, respectively. They were married in 1918 in Manteca, California, and had three children: Ruth Lee, Richard Lee, and Irene Lee. The family lived both in Manteca and in San Dimas prior to moving to Los Angeles. Nancy Lee's brother, Karl T. Kim (1895- ), lived with the family for a period of time. Both Joseph Lee and Nancy Lee died in Alameda, California.</p>
      </bioghist>
